## The Golden Rule

**Never hardcode user-facing text.** Every string a user can read ã labels, headings, placeholders, error messages, aria-labels, tooltips, button text ã must come from a translation key.

---

## Namespaces

| Namespace | File | Purpose | When to use |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `common` | `common.json` | Shared strings used across multiple pages/components | Navigation, actions (Save, Cancel), sidebar labels, masthead, shared UI elements |
| `pages` | `pages.json` | Page-specific strings | Content unique to a single page or feature |
| `marty` | `marty.json` | AI assistant (Marty) strings | Chat UI, assistant prompts, AI-related labels |

**Rule**: `common` is the default namespace. If you call `useTranslation()` with no argument, it reads from `common.json`.

---

## How to Add Translatable Strings

### Step 1: Add keys to ALL three language files

When adding a new string, you must add the key to `en`, `es`, and `fr` simultaneously. Never add a key to only one language.

```jsonc
// client/locales/en/common.json
{
  "myFeature": {
    "title": "My Feature",
    "description": "This feature does something useful."
  }
}

// client/locales/es/common.json
{
  "myFeature": {
    "title": "Mi funcionalidad",
    "description": "Esta funcionalidad hace algo û¤til."
  }
}

// client/locales/fr/common.json
{
  "myFeature": {
    "title": "Ma fonctionnalitûˋ",
    "description": "Cette fonctionnalitûˋ fait quelque chose d'utile."
  }
}
```

### Step 2: Use the `useTranslation` hook in your component

```tsx
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

export function MyFeature() {
  // For common namespace (default):
  const { t } = useTranslation();

  // For pages namespace:
  const { t } = useTranslation('pages');

  return (
    <h1>{t('myFeature.title')}</h1>
  );
}
```

### Step 3: When using multiple namespaces in one component

```tsx
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

export function MyPage() {
  const { t } = useTranslation();           // common namespace
  const { t: tp } = useTranslation('pages'); // pages namespace

  return (
    <div>
      <button>{t('actions.save')}</button>       {/* from common.json */}
      <h1>{tp('myPage.title')}</h1>              {/* from pages.json */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

