## Key Naming Conventions

### Structure

Keys are organized as nested objects grouped by feature or section:

```
namespace.section.key
```

### Rules

| Rule | Correct | Wrong |
|------|---------|-------|
| Use camelCase for keys | `campaignName` | `campaign-name`, `Campaign_Name` |
| Group by feature/section | `dataTable.colStatus` | `colStatus` |
| Be descriptive but concise | `searchPlaceholder` | `sp`, `theSearchInputPlaceholderText` |
| Use consistent suffixes | `title`, `description`, `label`, `placeholder`, `error`, `ariaLabel` | Mixing conventions |
| Keep nesting to 2-3 levels max | `myFeature.form.nameLabel` | `myFeature.form.fields.name.label.text` |

### Common key suffixes

| Suffix | Use for | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `title` | Page/section headings | `catalog.title` |
| `description` | Descriptive/body text | `catalog.description` |
| `label` | Form field labels | `form.emailLabel` |
| `placeholder` | Input placeholders | `form.emailPlaceholder` |
| `error` | Error messages | `form.emailError` |
| `ariaLabel` | Accessibility labels | `sidebar.expandAriaLabel` |
| `tooltip` | Tooltip text | `actions.deleteTooltip` |
| `empty` | Empty state messages | `table.emptyMessage` |

