## Which Namespace to Use

### Use `common` when:

- The string is reused across 2+ pages (nav items, action buttons, shared labels)
- It belongs to the app shell (masthead, sidebar, language selector)
- It is a generic UI pattern (Save, Cancel, Close, Loading...)

### Use `pages` when:

- The string is specific to a single page or feature
- It describes page-specific content (column headers, section titles unique to that view)
- It is demo/example content tied to a specific page

### Use `marty` when:

- The string is related to the AI assistant feature

**When in doubt, use `pages`** ã it is easier to promote a key to `common` later than to untangle shared keys.

---

## What Must Be Translated

### Always translate

- Headings and titles
- Button labels and link text
- Form field labels, placeholders, and helper text
- Error and validation messages
- Toast / notification messages
- Empty state text
- Table column headers
- Tab labels
- Breadcrumb text
- Tooltip and popover content
- `aria-label` attributes
- `alt` text on images
- Status text (Live, Paused, Completed, etc.)

### Do NOT translate

- Brand names and product names (Walmart, Marty)
- Technical identifiers (CSS class names, IDs, enum values)
- URLs and email addresses
- Code examples and syntax
- Icon-only content (use `aria-label` for the accessible name ã and translate that)
- Numeric-only values (currency amounts, dates are handled by formatters, not translation keys)

